                                <td><%= row.sample_id %></td>
                                <td><%= row.pe_seq %></td>
                                <td><%= row.total_reads %></td>
                                <td><%= row.avg_len %></td>
                                <td><%= row.data_bp %></td>
                                <td><%= row.data_mb %></td>
                            </tr>
                            <% }) %>
                        <% } %>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>
            <p><strong>Reads are provided in data deliverables folder “<em>00_Raw_data</em>”. Data was filtered to remove adapter and low-quality reads. Clean high quality (HQ) reads thus obtained was used for analysis.</strong></p>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 8 -->
        <div id="section-8" class="section">
            <h2>8. Bioinformatics Analysis</h2>

            <div id="section-8-1">
                <h3>8.1 QIIME2 Overview and steps for 16S analysis</h3>
                <p>Data was subjected to analysis by QIIME 2, which is an open-source microbiome data science platform. It is improved version of QIIME and it provides new features for analysis of the next generation of microbiome research. QIIME 2 is developed based on a plugin architecture that allows third parties to contribute functionality.</p>
                
                <div class="table-wrapper">
                    <div class="table-title">Table 2: QIIME2 plugins used for Analysis</div>
                    <table>
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th style="width: 30%;">Plugin</th>
                                <th>Function</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr><td>demux</td><td>Plugin for demultiplexing & viewing sequence quality</td></tr>
                            <tr><td>cutadapt</td><td>Plugin for removing adapter sequences, primers, and other unwanted sequence from sequence data</td></tr>
                            <tr><td>vsearch</td><td>Plugin for joining paired-end clustering and dereplicating with vsearch</td></tr>
                            <tr><td>quality-filter</td><td>Plugin for PHRED-based filtering and trimming</td></tr>
                            <tr><td>deblur</td><td>Plugin for sequence quality control with Deblur</td></tr>
                            <tr><td>feature-table</td><td>Plugin for working with sample by feature tables</td></tr>
                            <tr><td>feature-classifier</td><td>Plugin for taxonomic classification</td></tr>
                            <tr><td>taxa</td><td>plugin provides functionality for working with and visualizing taxonomic annotations of features</td></tr>
                            <tr><td>fragment-insertion</td><td>Plugin for extending phylogenies.</td></tr>
                            <tr><td>diversity</td><td>Plugin for exploring community diversity</td></tr>
                            <tr><td>Q2-krona</td><td>Plugin for plotting krona graph</td></tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>

                <h4>Below described are the steps executed during analysis through QIIME:</h4>
                <ol>
                    <li>Importing of demultiplexed paired-end fastq data as QIIME 2 artifacts</li>
                    <li>Joining of forward and reverse reads into single sequence</li>
                    <li>Filtering of joined reads based on quality to remove low-quality reads</li>
                    <li>Denoising the reads to correct it and get amplicon sequence variants (ASVs) with a 16S reference (88% OTUs from Greengenes 138) as a positive filter. The reference is only used to assess whether each sequence is likely to be 16S by a local alignment using SortMeRNA with a permissive e-value; the reference is not used to characterize the sequences</li>
                    <li>Assigning taxonomy to ASVs against V3-V4 region of SILVA 138 database. Here, "classifysklearn" was used which is a pre-fitted sklearn-based taxonomy classifier</li>
                    <li>Filtration of feature table to remove rare variants and contaminant (mitochondria) and unclassified ASVs as obtained after taxonomy assignment</li>
                    <li>Generating stacked barchart of taxa relative abundances</li>
                    <li>OTU heatmap generation at genus level</li>
                    <li>Building a tree with SEPP method for placing short sequences into a reference phylogenetic tree</li>
                    <li>Generating rarefaction curves to determine whether sufficient sequencing is done or not.</li>
                    <li>Calculating alpha and beta diversity metrics (if more than 2 samples)</li>
                    <li>Krona graph was then plotted using feature table and taxa information.</li>
                </ol>
            </div>

            <div id="section-8-2-1" style="margin-top: 30px;">
                <h3>8.2 Taxonomy Analysis</h3>
                <h4>8.2.1 Feature summary</h4>
                <div class="table-wrapper">
                    <div class="table-title">Table 3: Feature summary</div>
                    <table>
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th>Sample ID</th>
                                <th>PE seq</th>
                                <th>Joined filtered reads</th>
                                <th>Denoised reads (OTUs)</th>
                                <th>Filtered sequences*</th>
                                <th>Filtered feature count/OTUs*</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <% if (typeof metagenome_feature_summary !== 'undefined' && metagenome_feature_summary) { %>
                                <% metagenome_feature_summary.forEach(row => { %>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><%= row.sample_id %></td>
                                    <td><%= row.pe_seq %></td>
                                    <td><%= row.joined_filtered %></td>
                                    <td><%= row.denoised %></td>
                                    <td><%= row.filtered_seq %></td>
                                    <td><%= row.filtered_features %></td>
                                </tr>
                                <% }) %>
                            <% } %>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>
                <p style="font-size: 11px; color: var(--text-muted); font-style: italic;">
                    * Filtered sequences: Total sequences belonging to features remained after removing features consisting of single sequences as well as having mitochondrial hits.<br>
                    * Filtered feature count: Number of features remained after removing features consisting of single sequences as well as having mitochondrial hits.
                </p>
                <div class="info-box">
                    <strong>Further detail of above stats obtained can be found in data deliverables folders:</strong><br>
                    <code class="mono">01_Cutadapt_trimmed</code>, <code class="mono">02_PE_Joined_and_filtered</code>, <code class="mono">03_Deblur_denoised_feature</code>, <code class="mono">04_deblur_filter_contam</code>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div id="section-8-2-2" style="margin-top: 30px;">
                <h4>8.2.2 Taxonomy Distribution</h4>
                <p>Taxonomy distribution has been shown just of phylum level in the below mentioned graph and the table. However, complete taxonomy distribution at Phylum, Class, Order, Family, Genus, Species has been provided in data deliverables folder “<strong><em>05_Taxonomy_barplot</em></strong>”.</p>
                
                <% if (typeof metagenome_phylum_chart_src !== 'undefined' && metagenome_phylum_chart_src) { %>
                <div class="figure">
                    <img src="<%= metagenome_phylum_chart_src %>" alt="Comparative taxonomy at phylum level" />
                    <p class="caption">Figure 3: Comparative taxonomy at phylum level</p>
                </div>
                <% } %>

                <p style="font-style: italic;">Note: Images of other taxonomies (i.e from phylum level to species level) can be visualized from "<strong>05_Taxonomy_barplot/index.html</strong>". For changing the taxonomy level, change the level tab in the index.html.</p>

                <% if (typeof metagenome_taxonomy_distribution !== 'undefined' && metagenome_taxonomy_distribution) { %>
                <div class="table-wrapper">
                    <div class="table-title">Phylum taxonomic abundance details</div>
                    <table>
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <% metagenome_taxonomy_distribution.headers.forEach(h => { %>
                                <th><%= h %></th>
                                <% }) %>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <% metagenome_taxonomy_distribution.rows.forEach(row => { %>
                            <tr>
                                <% row.forEach((cell, i) => { %>
                                <td><%= cell %></td>
                                <% }) %>
                            </tr>
                            <% }) %>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>
                <% } %>
                <p style="font-size: 11px; font-style: italic; color: var(--text-muted);">
                    Note: Compiled phylum, class, order, family, genus, species count is provided in data deliverables excel file: level-2_taxa, level-3_taxa, level-4_taxa, level-5_taxa, level-6_taxa, level-7_taxa corresponding to phylum, class, order, family, genus, species respectively in folder “<strong>05_Taxonomy_barplot</strong>”.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div id="section-8-3" style="margin-top: 30px;">
                <h3>8.3 Feature/OTU heatmap</h3>
                <p>Feature-table plugging having heatmap module was used for generation of feature heatmap. For this, feature table was first collapsed at genus level. Heatmap representation of a feature table with clustering on features and samples axes was done after normalizing the feature table by adding a pseudo count of 1 and then taking the log10 of the table. Feature heatmap at different sequence cutoff is provided in data deliverables entitled <strong><em>"06_Feature_heatmap"</em></strong>.</p>
                
                <% if (typeof metagenome_heatmap_src !== 'undefined' && metagenome_heatmap_src) { %>
                <div class="figure">
                    <img src="<%= metagenome_heatmap_src %>" alt="OTU/feature heatmap" />
                    <p class="caption">Figure 4: OTU/feature heatmap (OTUs having minimum 500 sequence counts)</p>
                </div>
                <% } %>
            </div>

            <div id="section-8-4" style="margin-top: 30px;">
                <h3>8.4 α-Diversity</h3>
                <p>α-Diversity or within-sample diversity is calculated using a feature table which gives idea about species richness. Alpha diversity summarizes the diversity of organisms in a sample with a single number using different metrics in a habitat/sample. The below table summarizes the α-Diversity, where the columns correspond to alpha diversity metrics and the rows correspond to samples and their calculated diversity measurements. Data Deliverables for the same are provided entitled <strong><em>"08_Alpha_diversity"</em></strong>.</p>
                
                <div class="table-wrapper">
                    <div class="table-title">Table 5: Alpha-diversity statistics</div>
                    <table>
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th>Sample ID</th>
                                <th>Chao1 index</th>
                                <th>Shannon entropy</th>
                                <th>Observed features</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <% if (typeof metagenome_alpha_diversity !== 'undefined' && metagenome_alpha_diversity) { %>
                                <% metagenome_alpha_diversity.forEach(row => { %>
                                <tr>
                                    <td><%= row.sample_id %></td>
                                    <td><%= row.chao1 %></td>
                                    <td><%= row.shannon %></td>
                                    <td><%= row.observed_features %></td>
                                </tr>
                                <% }) %>
                            <% } %>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>

                <% if (typeof metagenome_alpha_plot_src !== 'undefined' && metagenome_alpha_plot_src) { %>
                <div class="figure">
                    <img src="<%= metagenome_alpha_plot_src %>" alt="Alpha diversity distribution plot" />
                    <p class="caption">Figure 5: Alpha-diversity distribution plot</p>
                </div>
                <% } %>
            </div>

            <div id="section-8-5" style="margin-top: 30px;">
                <h3>8.5 Rarefaction plot</h3>
                <p>Rarefaction allows the calculation of species richness for a given number of individual samples, based on the construction of so-called rarefaction curves. This curve is a plot of the number of species as a function of the number of samples. On the left, the steep slope indicates that a large fraction of the species diversity remains to be discovered. HTML file for rarefaction analysis is provided in data deliverables folder entitled <strong>"<em>09_Rarefaction_curve</em>"</strong>.</p>
                
                <% if (typeof metagenome_rarefaction_src !== 'undefined' && metagenome_rarefaction_src) { %>
                <div class="figure">
                    <img src="<%= metagenome_rarefaction_src %>" alt="Rarefaction plot" />
                    <p class="caption">Figure 6: Rarefaction plot (observed_features in metric)</p>
                </div>
                <% } %>
            </div>

            <div id="section-8-6" style="margin-top: 30px;">
                <h3>8.6 Beta Diversity</h3>
                <p>Beta diversity represents the explicit comparison of microbial communities based on their composition Beta-diversity metrics thus assess the differences between microbial communities. Beta diversity can be calculated through different statistical methods. Results obtained from all metrics is provided data deliverables folder <strong><em>“10_Beta_diversity”</em></strong>. Dissimilarity matrix and coordinate results obtained for Bray-Curtis is shown below:</p>
                
                <% if (typeof metagenome_beta_matrix !== 'undefined' && metagenome_beta_matrix) { %>
                <div class="table-wrapper">
                    <div class="table-title">Table 6: Bray Curtis Distance matrix</div>
                    <table>
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <% metagenome_beta_matrix.headers.forEach(h => { %>
                                <th><%= h %></th>
                                <% }) %>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <% metagenome_beta_matrix.rows.forEach(row => { %>
                            <tr>
                                <% row.forEach(cell => { %>
                                <td><%= cell %></td>
                                <% }) %>
                            </tr>
                            <% }) %>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>
                <% } %>

                <% if (typeof metagenome_pcoa_src !== 'undefined' && metagenome_pcoa_src) { %>
                <div class="figure">
                    <img src="<%= metagenome_pcoa_src %>" alt="Principal Coordinates Plot" />
                    <p class="caption">Figure 7: Principal Coordinates plot based on Bray-Curtis distance (first three principal axes)</p>
                </div>
                <% } %>
            </div>

            <div id="section-8-7" style="margin-top: 30px;">
                <h3>8.7 Krona graph</h3>
                <p>Krona is an interactive visualization tool for exploring the composition of metagenomes within a Web browser. Krona allows hierarchical metagenome data to be explored with zooming, multilayered pie charts. Krona graph was generated from feature table and taxonomy assigned by qiime2. Krona for all samples is provided as a part of data deliverables folder <strong><em>“11_Krona_graph/index.html”</em></strong>.</p>
                
                <% if (typeof metagenome_krona_src !== 'undefined' && metagenome_krona_src) { %>
                <div class="figure">
                    <img src="<%= metagenome_krona_src %>" alt="Krona graph representation" />
                    <p class="caption">Figure 8: Krona graph for sample representative species taxonomy</p>
                </div>
                <% } %>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 9 -->
        <div id="section-9" class="section">
            <h2>9. Data Deliverables</h2>
            <div class="table-wrapper">
                <div class="table-title">Deliverables Tree Structure</div>
                <div class="terminal-window">
                    <div class="terminal-header">
                        <span class="terminal-dot red"></span>
                        <span class="terminal-dot yellow"></span>
                        <span class="terminal-dot green"></span>
                        <span class="terminal-title">
                            <%= project_id %> — metagenome deliverables
                        </span>
                    </div>
                    <pre><%= deliverables_tree %></pre>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 10 -->
        <div id="section-10" class="section">
            <h2>10. Reference</h2>
            <p style="text-align: left; font-size: 12px; margin-bottom: 25px;">
                Bolyen, Evan, et al. "Reproducible, interactive, scalable and extensible microbiome data science using QIIME 2." <em>Nature biotechnology</em> 37.8 (2019): 852-857.
            </p>
            <p style="margin-top: 40px; font-weight: bold; text-align: center;">[END OF REPORT]</p>
        </div>

    </div>

    <button id="mobile-toc-toggle" onclick="toggleMobileSidebar()" aria-label="Toggle Navigation">☰</button>

    <!-- Floating Action Buttons -->
    <div style="position: fixed; bottom: 22px; right: 22px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 12px; z-index: 1010;" class="no-print">
        <button onclick="window.print()" title="Export to PDF / Print" style="width: 52px; height: 52px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--secondary-color); color: white; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; border: none; cursor: pointer; box-shadow: var(--card-shadow); transition: transform 0.2s ease;">
            <i data-lucide="printer" style="width: 22px; height: 22px;"></i>
        </button>
        <button onclick="window.scrollTo({top: 0, behavior: 'smooth'})" title="Back to top" style="width: 52px; height: 52px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--secondary-color); color: white; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; border: none; cursor: pointer; box-shadow: var(--card-shadow); transition: transform 0.2s ease;">
            <i data-lucide="arrow-up" style="width: 22px; height: 22px;"></i>
        </button>
    </div>

    <script>
        // Initialize Lucide icons
        lucide.createIcons();

        // Toggle Submenu with auto-collapsing siblings
        function toggleSubmenu(parentLi, forceExpand = null) {
            const submenu = parentLi.querySelector('.toc-submenu');
            const btn = parentLi.querySelector('.toc-toggle-btn');
            const row = parentLi.querySelector('.toc-row');

            if (!submenu) return;

            const isCurrentlyExpanded = submenu.classList.contains('expanded');
            const shouldExpand = forceExpand !== null ? forceExpand : !isCurrentlyExpanded;

            if (shouldExpand) {
                // Collapse siblings
                const siblingLis = Array.from(parentLi.parentElement.children).filter(el => el !== parentLi && el.classList.contains('has-children'));
                siblingLis.forEach(sib => {
                    const sibSubmenu = sib.querySelector('.toc-submenu');
                    const sibBtn = sib.querySelector('.toc-toggle-btn');
                    const sibRow = sib.querySelector('.toc-row');
                    if (sibSubmenu) sibSubmenu.classList.remove('expanded');
                    if (sibBtn) sibBtn.classList.remove('rotated');
                    if (sibRow) sibRow.classList.remove('active-row');
                });

                submenu.classList.add('expanded');
                if (btn) btn.classList.add('rotated');
                if (row) row.classList.add('active-row');
            } else {
                submenu.classList.remove('expanded');
                if (btn) btn.classList.remove('rotated');
                if (row) row.classList.remove('active-row');
            }
        }

        // Accordion click listeners
        document.querySelectorAll('.toc-toggle-btn').forEach(btn => {
            btn.addEventListener('click', function (e) {
                e.preventDefault();
                e.stopPropagation();
                const parentLi = this.closest('li.has-children');
                toggleSubmenu(parentLi);
            });
        });

        document.querySelectorAll('.toc-row a').forEach(link => {
            link.addEventListener('click', function (e) {
                const parentLi = this.closest('li.has-children');
                toggleSubmenu(parentLi);
            });
        });

        // Toggle mobile sidebar
        function toggleMobileSidebar() {
            const toc = document.getElementById('TOC');
            const btn = document.getElementById('mobile-toc-toggle');
            if (toc.classList.contains('open')) {
                toc.classList.remove('open');
                btn.innerHTML = '☰';
            } else {
                toc.classList.add('open');
                btn.innerHTML = '✕';
            }
        }

        // Close sidebar when clicking links on mobile
        document.querySelectorAll('#TOC a').forEach(link => {
            link.addEventListener('click', () => {
                const toc = document.getElementById('TOC');
                const btn = document.getElementById('mobile-toc-toggle');
                if (!link.closest('.toc-row')) {
                    if (toc.classList.contains('open')) {
                        toc.classList.remove('open');
                        btn.innerHTML = '☰';
                    }
                }

                // Immediately highlight active item
                document.querySelectorAll('#TOC a').forEach(a => a.classList.remove('active'));
                document.querySelectorAll('#TOC .toc-row').forEach(row => row.classList.remove('active-row'));

                const isMainLink = link.closest('.toc-row') || (link.parentElement.parentElement === document.querySelector('#TOC > ul'));
                if (isMainLink) {
                    link.classList.add('active');
                    const parentRow = link.closest('.toc-row');
                    if (parentRow) parentRow.classList.add('active-row');
                } else {
                    link.classList.add('active');
                    const parentLi = link.closest('#TOC > ul > li.has-children');
                    if (parentLi) {
                        const mainA = parentLi.querySelector('.toc-row a');
                        if (mainA) mainA.classList.add('active');
                        const mainRow = parentLi.querySelector('.toc-row');
                        if (mainRow) mainRow.classList.add('active-row');
                    }
                }
            });
        });

        // Scroll Spy active navigation highlight logic using getBoundingClientRect
        const sections = document.querySelectorAll('.main-container .section, .main-container .section [id^="section-8-"]');
        const navLinks = document.querySelectorAll('#TOC > ul > li > a, #TOC > ul > li > .toc-row > a, .toc-submenu a');

        window.addEventListener('scroll', () => {
            let current = '';
            sections.forEach(section => {
                const rect = section.getBoundingClientRect();
                if (rect.top <= window.innerHeight * 0.6) {
                    current = section.getAttribute('id');
                }
            });

            if (current) {
                // Map submenu active items to highlight parents
                let mappedCurrent = current;
                if (current.startsWith('section-8-')) {
                    mappedCurrent = current;
                }
                
                navLinks.forEach(link => {
                    link.classList.remove('active');
                    const parentRow = link.closest('.toc-row');
                    if (parentRow) parentRow.classList.remove('active-row');

                    if (link.getAttribute('href') === '#' + mappedCurrent) {
                        link.classList.add('active');
                        if (parentRow) parentRow.classList.add('active-row');
                        
                        // If it's a submenu item, auto-expand parent and highlight parent row too
                        const submenu = link.closest('.toc-submenu');
                        if (submenu) {
                            const parentLi = submenu.closest('li.has-children');
                            if (parentLi) {
                                toggleSubmenu(parentLi, true);
                                const mainA = parentLi.querySelector('.toc-row a');
                                if (mainA) mainA.classList.add('active');
                                const mainRow = parentLi.querySelector('.toc-row');
                                if (mainRow) mainRow.classList.add('active-row');
                            }
                        }
                    }
                });
            }
        }, { capture: true, passive: true });

        // Trigger once on load
        window.dispatchEvent(new Event('scroll'));

        // Scroll Progress Indicator Logic
        window.addEventListener('scroll', () => {
            const winScroll = document.body.scrollTop || document.documentElement.scrollTop;
            const height = document.documentElement.scrollHeight - document.documentElement.clientHeight;
            const scrolled = height > 0 ? (winScroll / height) * 100 : 0;
            const progressEl = document.getElementById('scroll-progress');
            if (progressEl) progressEl.style.width = scrolled + '%';
        });
    </script>

</body>

</html>
